<paragraph id="8BDF3692712CFFF2D9940A79FB3700C1" blockId="5.[174,1233,1303,1457]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">Diagnosis. The species is characterized by the weakly swollen and apically rounded clypeus; antenna with 14 flagellomeres, first flagellomere short, at most 3 times longer than width; propodeum with costulae present; stout legs with hind femora about 3.0–3.7 times longer than width, and smooth hind coxa; and tyloids on male flagellomeres 1–2(3).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712CFFF2D9940AF9FC6900E1" blockId="5.[174,1233,1303,1457]" box="[227,984,1430,1457]" pageId="5" pageNumber="490">
